<headline>Frost Advisory issued April 01 at 2:14PM EDT until April 02 at 9:00AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...FROST ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 2 AM TO 9 AM EDT SATURDAY...
* WHAT...Temperatures as low as 35 will result in frost
formation.
* WHERE...Much of the foothills and western Piedmont of North
Carolina and northern Upstate of South Carolina.
* WHEN...From 2 AM to 9 AM EDT Saturday.
* IMPACTS...Frost could kill sensitive outdoor vegetation if
left uncovered.</description>
<instruction>Take steps now to protect tender plants from the cold.</instruction>
